    {
        "content": "<p>The crucial point is integration by parts. This certainly can be done by hand using integration by parts for interval (the meat of the proof Jason mentioned is in <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/complex.Gamma_integral_add_one\">docs#complex.Gamma_integral_add_one</a> ), but the more structured approach would be to prove integration by parts for Schwartz functions</p>",
